<h2><b>Step 4: Promote Your Campaign</b></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Spread the word about your brick fundraising campaign through various channels. Leverage social media platforms, email marketing, and local community publications to reach a wide audience. Create compelling visuals and share success stories to engage potential donors and inspire them to support your cause.</span>
<h2><b>Step 5: Engage Your Community</b></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Make your fundraising campaign a community-wide effort by engaging local businesses, schools, and organizations. Collaborate with these stakeholders to promote your campaign and offer incentives for their participation. Encourage supporters to share their stories and testimonials about why they are purchasing engraved bricks, thus building a sense of community pride and connection.</span>
